    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <div class="last-updated">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 2025<br>
        <strong>Effective Date:</strong> June 2025
    </div>

    <div class="important">
        <strong>YOUR PRIVACY MATTERS:</strong> This Privacy Policy explains how Need4Me BeautyFast ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, discloses, and protects your personal information when you use our mobile application. By using the App, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect several types of information to provide and improve our services:</p>

        <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Name, email address, password when you create an account</li>
            <li><strong>Profile Information:</strong> Display name, bio, profile photo, favorite style preferences</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Information:</strong> Processed securely through Stripe (we do not store full credit card details)</li>
            <li><strong>Photos:</strong> Images you upload, edit, or create using the App</li>
            <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Messages you send us through customer support</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Information Automatically Collected</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> Device model, operating system, unique device identifiers, mobile network information</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Features used, filters applied, time spent in the App, crash logs, performance data</li>
            <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> Approximate location based on IP address (we do not collect precise GPS location)</li>
            <li><strong>Cookies and Similar Technologies:</strong> We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to analyze app usage</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.3 Information from Third Parties</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Social Media:</strong> If you sign in through Google or Facebook, we receive basic profile information from those platforms</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Providers:</strong> Transaction information from Stripe and Google Play / Apple App Store</li>
            <li><strong>Analytics Services:</strong> Data from Firebase Analytics and Google AdMob</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>

        <table>
            <tr>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Description</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Provide Services</strong></td>
                <td>Process your photos, apply filters and effects, save edited images</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Account Management</strong></td>
                <td>Create and maintain your account, authenticate users, manage subscriptions</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Improve the App</strong></td>
                <td>Analyze usage patterns, fix bugs, develop new features, optimize performance</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Customer Support</strong></td>
                <td>Respond to your inquiries, troubleshoot issues, provide technical assistance</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Marketing</strong></td>
                <td>Send promotional materials, notify you of new features (with your consent)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td><strong>Legal Compliance</strong></td>
                <td>Comply with legal obligations, enforce our Terms of Service, protect our rights</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>

        <h3>3.1 Service Providers</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Firebase:</strong> Cloud services, authentication, analytics</li>
            <li><strong>Google AdMob:</strong> Advertisement serving (see our advertising section below)</li>
            <li><strong>Stripe:</strong> Payment processing for premium subscriptions</li>
            <li><strong>Cloud Storage:</strong> If you enable cloud backup features</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Legal Requirements</h3>
        <p>We may disclose your information if required by law, court order, or government request, or to protect our rights, property, or safety.</p>

        <h3>3.3 Business Transfers</h3>
        <p>If Need4Me is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.</p>

        <h3>3.4 With Your Consent</h3>
        <p>We may share your information with third parties when you explicitly consent to such sharing.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>4. Your Photos and Content</h2>
        <div class="important">
            <strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Your photos are precious to us. Here's how we handle them:
        </div>

        <p><strong>4.1 Local Storage:</strong> By default, all photos are stored locally on your device. We do not upload your photos to our servers unless you explicitly use cloud backup features.</p>

        <p><strong>4.2 Processing:</strong> When you apply filters or effects, photo processing happens on your device. We do not send your photos to external servers for processing.</p>

        <p><strong>4.3 Ownership:</strong> You retain full ownership and copyright of your photos. We do not claim any rights to your photos.</p>

        <p><strong>4.4 Sharing:</strong> If you choose to share photos through the App (e.g., on social media), you control what is shared and where.</p>

        <p><strong>4.5 Deletion:</strong> When you delete photos from the App, they are permanently removed from your device. If you use cloud backup, you can delete photos from cloud storage through your account settings.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>5. Advertising and Analytics</h2>
        <p><strong>5.1 Google AdMob:</strong> We use Google AdMob to display advertisements in the free version of the App. AdMob may collect device information, ad interactions, and other data to serve personalized ads. You can opt out of personalized advertising through your device settings.</p>

        <p><strong>5.2 Firebase Analytics:</strong> We use Firebase to analyze app usage, user behavior, and performance metrics. This helps us improve the App experience.</p>

        <p><strong>5.3 Your Choices:</strong></p>
        <ul>
            <li>Upgrade to Premium ($3.88/month) to remove ads</li>
            <li>Opt out of personalized ads in your device settings (Android: Google Settings → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization)</li>
            <li>Limit ad tracking on iOS devices through Settings → Privacy → Advertising</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction:</p>

        <ul>
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> Data transmitted between the App and our servers is encrypted using SSL/TLS</li>
            <li><strong>Secure Storage:</strong> Account information is stored securely with industry-standard encryption</li>
            <li><strong>Access Controls:</strong> We limit access to personal information to authorized personnel only</li>
            <li><strong>Regular Audits:</strong> We conduct regular security assessments and updates</li>
        </ul>

        <p>However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your information, we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide our services and fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy:</p>

        <ul>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> Retained until you delete your account</li>
            <li><strong>Photos:</strong> Stored on your device until you delete them; cloud backups retained until deletion</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Retained for up to 2 years for analytics purposes</li>
            <li><strong>Payment Records:</strong> Retained for 7 years for tax and legal compliance</li>
        </ul>

        <p>After the retention period, we will securely delete or anonymize your information.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>8. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal information:</p>

        <h3>8.1 Access and Correction</h3>
        <p>You can access and update your account information through the App's profile settings.</p>

        <h3>8.2 Data Portability</h3>
        <p>You can export your photos and data from the App at any time.</p>

        <h3>8.3 Deletion</h3>
        <p>You can delete your account and all associated data by going to Settings → Account → Delete Account. This action is permanent and cannot be undone.</p>

        <h3>8.4 Opt-Out of Marketing</h3>
        <p>You can opt out of promotional emails by clicking the unsubscribe link in any marketing email or adjusting your notification settings in the App.</p>

        <h3>8.5 California Residents (CCPA)</h3>
        <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Know what personal information we collect and how it is used</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your personal information</li>
            <li>Opt out of the sale of personal information (note: we do not sell personal information)</li>
            <li>Non-discrimination for exercising your privacy rights</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.6 European Residents (GDPR)</h3>
        <p>If you are in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have additional rights under GDPR, including the right to object to processing and the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.</p>

        <p><strong>To exercise your rights, contact us at:</strong> support@need4mebeautyfast@gmail.com</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p><strong>Age Restriction:</strong> Need4Me BeautyFast is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.</p>

        <p>If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13 without parental consent, we will promptly delete that information.</p>

        <p><strong>Parental Consent:</strong> If you are between 13 and 18 years old, you must have parental or guardian permission to use the App.</p>

        <p>If you believe a child under 13 has provided personal information to us, please contact us immediately at support@need4mebeautyfast@gmail.com.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>10. International Data Transfers</h2>
        <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. These countries may have data protection laws that are different from your home country.</p>

        <p>When we transfer your information internationally, we take appropriate safeguards to ensure your information remains protected in accordance with this Privacy Policy and applicable laws.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>11. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>The App may contain links to third-party websites or services (e.g., social media platforms). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy policies before providing any personal information.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. When we make material changes, we will:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy</li>
            <li>Notify you through the App or by email</li>
            <li>Request your consent if required by law</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Your continued use of the App after changes become effective constitutes your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>13. Do Not Track Signals</h2>
        <p>Some web browsers have a "Do Not Track" feature that signals to websites you visit that you do not want to have your online activity tracked. Currently, we do not respond to Do Not Track signals, as there is no industry standard for how to handle such signals.</p>
    </div>

